<br>
When I started wich was a year ago it was already changed (I think). I was tired of the other games I played and wanted something new to play with so went to the store to buy a new game. I had a very vague idea what Everquest was about from a random article and hear saying.<br>
<br>
I just bought the game and didn't do research or rulesets and stuff cause I had no idea what the game was actually about. I just installed, logged on and then got confrontated with 15 different servers to choose from.<br>
<br>
2 servers stood out, Antonios Bayle cause it was &quot;Europian server&quot; and Firiona Vie cause it was Roleplay Prefered. You know what I picked.<br>
<br>
I started out with roleplaying but now I don't care anymore, I just want to play the game on the server I like with the gear I earned.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syllestraefv>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 2603<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/1/03 5:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3840.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Can I ask what brought this change about?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
After being around for a few months, the server population was lower than they anticipated.<br>
<br>
They felt the reason the population was low was because some of the rules made it too difficult to play here, particularly for players new to EQ, so they dropped them.<br>
<br>
The fact that even after the removal of the rules the population never skyrocketed, and the fact that other new servers are likewise suffering on population, points towards the EQ populace settling in to their existing servers.  There's enough content available that old servers don't have the crowding that they used to, so there's not much alleviation gained by moving to a new one.  People can stay where they are and play just fine.<br>
<br>
The experiment didn't fail, there's just not a lot of motive for people to leave their servers anymore.  With Kunark, Velious, Luclin, Planes of Power, LoY, and the optional zones (Stonebrunt, Jaggedpine, Warrens, etc) the servers can support a lot more players than they used to.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dairyu>DaiRyu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/1/03 5:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3840.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> So how do you fix it?</span><hr size=1> In some way they were right.  There were very few people on at any given time and this made it hard to find a group especially since you could only group with some of the people and only understand a small number of those you could.<br>
<br>
Do I wish we still had alignments?  Yes, I wish that the alignment was desplayable next to the name ALL the time like a guild tag.  If you don't care, turn it off.  If you do care, then there you go.  On the other hand xp bonuses and penalties and the inability to group with people of disperate views is not going to work for most people.<br>
<br>
As to the language barrier, that was also a bit far.  Cap the language at level x 5 + 5 and let the rest of the learning be as normal.  People hate not being able to understand, it makes them paranoid that they are being talked about.<br>
<br>
I REALLY wish they would reinstate the limited range shout rule, nothing worse than stepping into a zone and getting nothing but red text.  Well except getting harm touched by that damn Unicorn...<br>
<br>
With the new UI many of these problems can be avoided by makeing a new text window but it would be nice to have commerce restricted once more, it seems odd to me to be in south Karana and some one is selling pies.<br>
<br>
The biggest thing is they need to get more GM/guides on &quot;fixing&quot; names.  The stupid names that people choose, and think they are being cute or funny or whatever is just sad and distracting.<br>
<br>
Oh well...at least this server is still better than 99% of all other servers.  I do kinda wish they had gone to 3 characters per account though...<br>
